abstract: Democrats have won every statewide election since 2002, and have seized control of the State Senate; now the Republican state party chairman, Ed Cox, is leaving.
snippet: Democrats have won every statewide election since 2002, and have seized control of the State Senate; now the Republican state party chairman, Ed Cox, is leaving.
lead_paragraph: The last time New York’s Republican Party won a race for statewide office, Andrew M. Cuomo’s political career was a mess, Donald J. Trump’s political career didn’t exist and George E. Pataki was cruising to a third term as governor.

abstract: The prosecution of President Andrew Johnson in 1868 was an attempt to restore faith in America’s original ideals.
snippet: The prosecution of President Andrew Johnson in 1868 was an attempt to restore faith in America’s original ideals.
lead_paragraph: When we talk about whether to impeach President Trump, we cite the near impeachment of Richard Nixon or the actual prosecution of Bill Clinton. Oddly, though, we don’t talk much about the first-ever presidential impeachment, which very nearly succeeded in removing Andrew Johnson from office.

abstract: This week’s Canada Letter features excerpts from The Times’s recent interview with Canada’s prime minister, whose political fortunes have fallen.
snippet: This week’s Canada Letter features excerpts from The Times’s recent interview with Canada’s prime minister, whose political fortunes have fallen.
lead_paragraph: Last month I sat down with Prime Minister Justin Trudeau for an extended interview, the first since his government had been rocked by the resignations and political turmoil created by its handling of SNC-Lavalin’s criminal prosecution.

lead_paragraph: Every Friday, pop critics for The New York Times weigh in on the week’s most notable new songs and videos. Just want the music? Listen to the Playlist on Spotify here (or find our profile: nytimes). Like what you hear? Let us know at theplaylist@nytimes.com and sign up for our Louder newsletter, a once-a-week blast of our pop music coverage.

abstract: The New York senator is mired near the bottom of most polls but hopes to jump-start her campaign and fund-raising as she aggressively criticizes anti-abortion laws in Alabama and other states.
snippet: The New York senator is mired near the bottom of most polls but hopes to jump-start her campaign and fund-raising as she aggressively criticizes anti-abortion laws in Alabama and other states.
lead_paragraph: In the two years leading up to her 2020 run, Senator Kirsten Gillibrand spent millions of dollars building up a network of online and grass-roots donors who could power her coming presidential campaign.

abstract: His poll standings are in free fall, and a dispute with a female cabinet minister raised questions about his leadership, but the Canadian prime minister remains confident.
snippet: His poll standings are in free fall, and a dispute with a female cabinet minister raised questions about his leadership, but the Canadian prime minister remains confident.
lead_paragraph: OTTAWA — Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada has a simple strategy for winning re-election: Ignore the plummeting polls, defend his record and push back against detractors.
